notesStmt.note: Folio 120v: Psalterium istud est Monasterii Sancti Benedicti.
Monastery of Sancta Maria de angelis in Florence and of Sanct Benedict outside the walls in Florence, inscribed as owners of this psaltery in several Latin notes on folios 1v, 3r, 120v.
Folio 121v, records of birth, with a date of 5422 (1662).
Manuscript description based on Margoliouth, G.: Catalogue of the Hebrew and Samaritan Manuscripts in the British Museum, London 1965.

layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 2; ruled lines: 11; written lines: 11; Uniform layout. The Latin beginnings of the Psalms marked in the margins. Masorah magna occupies 1 line in the upper margin and up to 2 lines in the lower margin, sometimes written in an ornamental pattern. Visible pricking and folio by folio ruling with a hard-point. Hair side and flesh side of folios distinguishable.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Fine Sefardi square script, punctuated, of the 14th century.

binding.p: BL in-house. Spine: 'Psalterium. Hebrew. British Library. Additional 18830.'
